      "analysis_source": "llm-per-reviewer",
      "patch_summary": "This patch series (v4) aims to switch the THP shrinker from its current open-coded deferred split queue to using the list_lru data structure. The existing implementation has issues, including being non-NUMA-aware and complicated in its interactions with other code. Switching to list_lru fixes these problems, simplifies the code, and streamlines the interaction between the THP shrinker and LRU state. The series includes several cleanup patches (1-4) that prepare for this change, followed by extensions to the list_lru API (5-6) and finally the switch itself in patch 8."
